.so fork.tmac
.SS START ACTION
.PP
The
.B start
action sets
.B pwb
in motion.
From this point,
.B pwb
will call script functions to construct the screen and
respond to user input.
.PP
.pt_start
.PP
.B OPTIONS
.RS 4
.TP
.I handle
is the name of a declared
.B pwb
handle.
.TP
.BI "-t " top_row
Integer value specifying the table index of the starting top row
in the content area.  The default value is 0.
.TP
.BI "-f " focus_row
Integer value specifying the table index of the starting focus row
in the content area.  The default value is 0.
.TP
.BI "-b " base_keymap
Use the option to specify an alternative to the builtin keymap.
The default keymap handles navigation between rows, pages, and the
document using arrow, page, home, and end keys, and terminates upon
detecting the 'q' key.
.TP
.BI "-a " auxiliary_keymap
Is an optional second keymap that can act on defined keystrokes
to execute the users' wishes.
.TP
.BI "-k " ending_keypress
If provided,
.B pwb
will set this named variable with the keystroke that terminated
the interaction.
.RE
.B NOTES
.RS 4
.TP
.B Margins
If setting margins, it is advised to set the margins before calling
the
.B start
action.
If the margins are changed after calling
.BR "pwb start" ,
follow
.BR "pwb set_margins " with " pwb print_all"
to align the content to the updated settings.
See
.B SET_MARGINS ACTION
below.
.TP
.B Empty Data Source
Calling
.B pwb start
with an empty data source will result in a blank screen.  The best
practice, if an empty data source is possible, is to recognize the
empty data and display a explanation instead of calling
.BR "pwb start" .
.RE
